  3. Error Handling During Migration

  Migration Script Approach

  Instead of running individual bash commands, create a migration script that handles errors gracefully:

  #!/bin/bash
  # theme_migration.sh

  set -e  # Exit on any error

  migrate_theme() {
      local theme_name=$1
      echo "Migrating theme: $theme_name"

      # Create backup first
      if [ ! -d "theme/${theme_name}.backup" ]; then
          cp -r "theme/${theme_name}" "theme/${theme_name}.backup"
          echo "✓ Backup created"
      fi

      # Check if source files exist before moving
      if [ -d "theme/${theme_name}/includes/css" ]; then
          mkdir -p "theme/${theme_name}/assets/css"
          mv "theme/${theme_name}/includes/css"/* "theme/${theme_name}/assets/css/" 2>/dev/null || true
          echo "✓ CSS files moved"
      fi

      # Continue with other moves...
      echo "✓ Theme $theme_name migrated successfully"
  }

  # Rollback function
  rollback_theme() {
      local theme_name=$1
      echo "Rolling back theme: $theme_name"
      rm -rf "theme/${theme_name}"
      mv "theme/${theme_name}.backup" "theme/${theme_name}"
      echo "✓ Theme $theme_name rolled back"
  }

  Fallback Strategy

  During transition, keep old asset paths working by creating symbolic links:
  # After migration, create compatibility links
  ln -s ../assets/css theme/falcon/includes/css
  ln -s ../assets/js theme/falcon/includes/js

  4. Migration Validation

  Automated Validation Script

  #!/bin/bash
  # validate_migration.sh

  validate_theme() {
      local theme_name=$1
      local errors=0

      echo "Validating theme: $theme_name"

      # 1. Check required directories exist
      for dir in "assets/css" "assets/js" "assets/images" "views"; do
          if [ ! -d "theme/${theme_name}/${dir}" ]; then
              echo "❌ Missing directory: ${dir}"
              ((errors++))
          fi
      done

      # 2. Check PHP syntax
      find "theme/${theme_name}" -name "*.php" -exec php -l {} \; | grep -v "No syntax errors" && ((errors++))

      # 3. Check for old asset references in PHP files
      if grep -r "includes/css\|includes/js" "theme/${theme_name}"/*.php 2>/dev/null; then
          echo "❌ Found old asset references"
          ((errors++))
      fi

      # 4. Check assets directory isn't empty
      if [ -z "$(find "theme/${theme_name}/assets" -name "*" -type f 2>/dev/null)" ]; then
          echo "❌ Assets directory is empty"
          ((errors++))
      fi

      if [ $errors -eq 0 ]; then
          echo "✅ Theme $theme_name validation passed"
          return 0
      else
          echo "❌ Theme $theme_name validation failed with $errors errors"
          return 1
      fi
  }

  Manual Validation Checklist

  After each migration, verify:
